<item>
            <title>[LU-6212] listxattr() on HSM released file does not return lustre.lov</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6212</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For a regular file ll_listxattr() will only emit a lustre.lov xattr name if the member lli_has_smd of the associated lli is true. lli_has_smd is initialized using lsm_has_objects() which returns false for released LSMs. Hence an HSM released file does not return lustre.lov from listxattr().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Explicitly calling getxattr() to request lustre.lov will return the attribute. But it will not have the correct stripe count. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6211&quot; title=&quot;getxattr() for {lustre,trusted}.lov on HSM released file returns stripe count 0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6211&quot;&gt;LU-6211&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
